{{Infobox university | name = Musikene | image = Musikene.jpg | image_size= 250px | caption = Musikene's seat, in [[San Sebastián]]. | established = 2001 | type = [[Private school|Private]] | head_name = | head = | faculty = | enrollment = | free_label = | free = | free_label1 = | free1 = | affiliations = | city = [[San Sebastián]] | state = [[Basque Country (autonomous community)|Basque Country]] | country = [[Spain]] | website = [http://musikene.eus/ musikene.eus] | coor = }}
'''Musikene''' or the '''Higher School of Music of the Basque Country''' ([[Basque language|Basque]] - ''Euskal Herriko Goi-Mailako Musika Ikastegia''; [[Spanish language|Spanish]] - ''Centro Superior de Música del País Vasco'') is a [[higher education]] [[music school]] located in [[San Sebastián]], in the [[Basque Country (autonomous community)|Basque region]] of [[Spain]]. It was founded in 2001 by the [[Basque Government]] through the establishment of a private foundation.
The school was housed on the [[Miramar Palace]]. In 2012, the construction of a new building, which houses the school since the 2016-2017 academic year, began next to the San Sebastián campus of the [[University of the Basque Country]].
==External links== *[http://musikene.eus/ Musikene official website]
